Description: Up for grabs is a nice 1998 AR200 by Ibanez! The AR200 is an Artist series solid body electric guitar model introduced by Ibanez in 1998. The AR200 has all the basic Artist features but unlike most models which proceeded it in the series, it was produced outside Japan. It features a mahogany body with a maple top with binding mated to a set-in maple neck with a 22-fret bound rosewood fingerboard with dot position markers. Components include a fixed bridge and tailpiece and dual Ibanez Axis humbucking pickups with individual volume and tone controls. This guitar is used but in good shape. There is some light fretwear, some light scratching, and a good sized ding on the back and bottom part of the body.
